data.description: This custom-built, two-story home with western exposure capitalizes on wide interior and breathtaking sunset views overlooking Lake Alhambra in sought-after Cape Coral. Sitting on .23 acres, the home boasts nearly 2,500 square feet with 4 bedrooms and 2.5 baths. The structure features upgraded flooring throughout the first floor and stairway and the addition of stainless-steel appliances. Situated on perhaps the most interesting freshwater system in Cape Coral, you can spend the day boating. When not on the water, you can spend time in an oversized in-ground pool equipped with a solar heater allowing for comfortable swimming year-round. A pass-through window from the lanai to the kitchen, as well as two pocket sliders, open the backside of the home for panoramic lake views and comfortable breezes. Living room’s focal point is a stone fireplace rising to the top of the vaulted ceiling, saving on heating costs. A spacious kitchen includes granite counter tops, flat-top range with stainless steel overhead hood and considerable storage. Two-car garage includes built-in shelves. Home is not in a flood zone, so no flood insurance required. No HOA.
